article.headline: Illinois State 66, Cal State Northridge 44
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Dominitrix Johnson scored 16 points, 12 of them on 4-of-7 three-point shooting, and Boo Richardson added 15 as Illinois State beat Cal State-Northridge 66-44 Monday night. Anthony Slack chipped in 12 points and a team-high seven rebounds for the Redbirds (2-2), who managed 27 points off Cal State-Northridge turnovers. Richardson was 6-for-7 from the foul line. The Matadors (4-2) were led by 14 points from Calvin Chitwood. Jayme Miller added 10 off the bench, the team's only other player in double figures, before fouling out with 1:43 to go in the game. A 12-5 Cal State-Northridge run to end the contest made little difference after Illinois State took a 36-16 advantage into halftime and only built on it, leading by as many as 29 points with 5:15 remaining. The Redbirds set a new home record for holding the Matadors to the lowest field goal percentage by an opponent (25.9) and tied the record for fewest field goals made by a visiting team (14).
